details.description: August Lily Florist proudly serving the Monroe, North Carolina area since 2009, offering a wide variety of fresh floral arrangements and gifts to suit any style, occasion and budget. We're happy to assist you with local and worldwide deliveries, including daily deliveries to local funeral homes and hospitals. We are a family-owned local business that is dedicated to the well being of our community. Our shop is a fresh new twist on an old local building. We have renovated a 100 year old residence on Benton Street to house fresh flowers, silk flowers, plants, artwork and an assortment of gifts.

reviews_data.review_text: Super cute spot! The baklava latte is delicious and they have a great selection of gifts and pretty bouquets to purchase!
Beautiful environment, kind employees, and great service. I got the Southern Charm (I think?) coffee and I will be thinking about how good it was for probably the rest of my life. 10/10 experience.
Best cafe ever! Such a warm and friendly environment. They have the best collection of pastries and beautiful plants. They make the world's best London Fog latte.

This is the CUTEST coffee shop I’ve had in the area, coming from a local. The coffee was top tier, delicious and was handcrafted with the smallest attention to details (the ice cubes are coffee balls so your drink doesn’t get watered down as it melts!!!!) They have options for non coffee drinkers as well as dirty sodas (not alcohol just mixed flavors- I didn’t try thee but thought it was neat) The actual shop is a real florist and you can purchase bouquets, and potted flowers. And it is so cozy and cute inside. Seriously the best coffee shop around, a must try for coffee lovers in the Monroe area 10/10

This is such a cute coffee spot. The little details are everything 😍 I love that they add a flower cutting to the cups. There's a wide variety of bouquets and plants to choose from. Great place for gifts!

Although Google lists it as a florist, you’ll quickly discover it’s much more than that. Nestled inside a charming old house, this hidden gem offers both a stunning selection of flowers and a cozy little coffee shop tucked right inside.

All of their drinks and small bites are fresh, homemade, and absolutely delicious. They also feature a rotating seasonal menu, and somehow every new item is better than the last—it never disappoints.

One of the sweetest touches? They tape a little dried flower to your cup. It’s such a simple but thoughtful detail that makes your visit feel special.
If you have a little extra time, I highly recommend grabbing a seat in what was probably once the home’s living room. You can sip your coffee near the fireplace and just enjoy the quiet charm of the space. August Lilly is truly one of a kind.

Took my daughter to August Lily Florist in Monroe and we absolutely loved it! What a wonderful and refreshing niche, combining a florist with a cozy café. The space is beautiful, the flowers are stunning, and the atmosphere is warm and welcoming. It's such a lovely spot to spend time together, whether you're picking out blooms or just enjoying a drink and a treat.  I only wish they had more indoor seating.  The good news is I was told they are expanding the seating area. Highly recommend for a sweet outing or a little self-care stop!
The most cutest coffee shop! Beautiful flowers and plants for sale as well.

Really nice place. They sell a good variety of coffee and specialty drinks. They also have sweet treats and baked goods. The star product is most definitely the plants. They have a good selection of small to mid size house plants, along with cut flowers. All the plants are given personal names, which is super cute. The staff is awesome and really helpful. I'll definitely be back for flowers and coffee!
I got the Carmel frappe with espresso and I didn’t realize that it comes with a mini flower on the cup

Brilliant coffee shoppe masquerading as a florist! 🥰😋 Seriously good espresso drinks in a beautiful setting with fresh-baked treats and a local-inspired gift shop and all things floral. Inside and out seating are peaceful reminders to slow down and take a deep breath and a sip of fresh-roasted goodness!
5 Star Coffee Shop!!!
Worked great for me
Super cute place!! The coffee and staff are amazing. Awesome place for a little girls date
My favorite place and Coffee.

I just discovered this coffee shop/ flower shop and love everything about it. It's such a refreshing atmosphere enjoying your coffee surrounded by plants. Plus, the coffee is pretty good with baked goods available.

Wow! First time here today and I will go out of my way to come back. The atmosphere is so cute and relaxing. I got the banana nut bread latte and LOVED it. I’ve tried a LOT of coffee shops in the Charlotte area and this was in my top 5 drinks. And a little flower taped on the cup? Love love love. I’ll be back, and I’ll bring some friends next time!
Botanical beauty and bold flavors! Great coffee and gorgeous flower arrangements. Thank you August Lily baristas and florists.

The cutest place ever! I love that her niche is coffee and flowers. The owners design skill makes this place adorable and cozy. Perfect to sit in for a nice cup of coffee, tea or iced drink. I love the dried flower she taped on every cup! Truly a thoughtful gesture.
Love love love this place. Stumbled across randomly one day in the Fall and have returned several times since. Great coffee, cute workspace, and beautiful & affordable plants and florals.

We were headed to SC and drove through Monroe.   My daughter suggested that we stop here this to get some coffee/matcha.   I'm very glad we stopped here.  It's an adorable flower and coffee shop with other cute merchandise.

We were welcomed by Morgan.   She was very friendly and helpful.

My daughter ordered an iced matcha and I had The Winnie (local honey, local vanilla milk and cinnamon) hot.  When we got our drink, we saw that she put a teeny tiny bouquet of flowers on them.  That put a smile on our faces. Our drinks were delicious!

Parking could be tricky.   If you are in Monroe,  definitely stop in.  Looking forward to coming back again soon.

They canceled my order at the last minute because they said they had nothing to fill a floral bouquet with. Very disappointed. Exercise caution when attempting to place an order. I tried to support local, but unfortunately they could not deliver - literally.

Hidden gem of monroe!! Will be coming back.
Coffee and pastries were soo good!
I highly recommend the Lavender black tea cake
Such a cozy atmosphere with nice people! Great coffee too!

A very nice place to go to if you have floral needs.  Quaint atmosphere almost bohemian. Good little coffee shop. And service is great too. A bit pricey though with unique pastries and chocolate and other baking types items.

An incredibly cute gift store / coffee shop. Tons of small details that make your first trip feel special. Their prices on their gifts are reasonably priced and have cheaper options if you don’t want to spend a ton!

Missed a call from them as they tried to make absolutely sure that my arrangement was as desired but they still delivered a gorgeous bouquet for delivery Monday when I ordered on a Saturday. Wonderful place
Love the place, and the coffee, the atmosphere are so relax and the flowers and plants are a plus , the pastry uff delicious and the staff so friendly definitely add to my favorite places.
I used August Lily Florist last Sunday for an arrangement for my son’s baptism. They out did themselves. The arrangement was gorgeous. I highly recommend them- my picture doesn’t do it justice

The coffee shop inside this florist is my new favorite spot. The signature drinks have unique twists and are tasty! Lots of treats from other local bakers to choose from as well to go along with the drinks. the decor/vibes are immaculate and all the ladies I've dealt with in there have been super nice!
This is my new found coffee place! The customer service is awesome and would recommend to come in and check it out!
Just picked up my daughter’s flowers  for her prom and they did an amazing  job! Exceeded my expectations! They were very pleasant and professional.

EXCELLENT!!!!!!!! Picked out some individual stems and Kim brought it to life with other added greenery! The flowers are very fresh and the pink roses smell sooooo good! Whole house smells of flowers this morning.
Beautiful arrangements, long lasting, gorgeous colors. Highly recommended!
Super friendly and great experience

August Lily is the only place I go for flowers, plants, decorations,  etc.  They are talented artists; and so friendly.  They actually listen to make arrangements suit to your taste.  I have never been disappointed....and I use them a lot.

Kim is the absolute best! She brought my vision to life better than I could have ever imagined. If you’re looking for a wedding florist, she’s your gal! Easy to communicate with and was able to create a masterpiece while remaining in our budget which felt like a miracle when wedding planning.

I purchased the bouquet for my wedding from August Lily and it was exactly how I imagined it. They were very professional and worked with me to make sure they had the right color rose. It was perfect! Thank you so much.

August Lilly is my go-to florist. They are so genuinely kind and helpful. They truly go above and beyond to exceed my expectations- even for last minute needs! I recommend them to everyone and use them for all of my floral needs. 10/10 recommend!!

Worked with Kim for my daughters wedding. All flowers were beautiful but she shorted us the throw away bouquet and the Maid of Honor Bouquet. We did not notice in time before the wedding. After wedding was told that we never ordered those bouquets. There was no written invoice as Kim was just writing on a scrap sheet of paper Just trusted her which was a big mistake.

You know how when you order online most places send something not even similar to what you thought you were ordering. Well not here, this place is fabulous and I was pleasantly surprised at how beautiful the arrangement was. I will always have them stored in my phone for anytime I need flowers. HIGHLY recommend!!!
Beautiful plants, cards and gifts!!  I love going there especially on holidays.  Will not disappoint.

August Lily was suggested to us for our daughter's wedding in December and what a great decision!  It was a small wedding and the only flowers we got was her bouquet but it was absolutely gorgeous!  They worked with us to create a bouquet that matched my daughter's vision but stayed within our budget.  We got so many comments on how beautiful the bouquet was, and it was!
Apart from that, because we were there in December, they had an amazing gift shop set up with so many cute things.   I went again last week on Valentines Day and they had their "Flower Hour" going all day where you could select individual stems at half price and create your own bouquet.
What a unique, fun, and creative flower shop!
(Photo by Aureola Spectrum Photography)

I wish I could give 10 stars. This is the first florist I’ve ever worked with and it was for my mom’s celebration of life. Kim was so thorough and understanding when I sent her a literal diagram of exactly what I was looking for. My mom loved flowers so this was very important for me to get it right to have around her urn and memory book display. Anything that Kim and her team didn’t have, she was quick to suggest either silk or another flower similar. Communication was amazing, she answered any questions my family and I had. Couldn’t have asked for someone easier to work with for such a hard time in our lives. The flowers were beautifully done, thank you so much August Lily Team ♥️

I wanted to use a local florist instead of FTD and that was a mistake. I ordered an $85 arrangement, and a picture was provided of the price point I paid, which was the middle one. The one that was delivered was less than half the size of the one in the picture. I sent a message and heard nothing back. Why bother supporting local businesses when they are no better than the chains?

I am a Charlotte wedding photographer and had the pleasure of working with August Lily Florist in Oct 2021! All the floral designs from the bouquets, boutonnières, ceremony arbor, and reception tablescapes, was STUNNING!! I was blown away by all the attention to detail. The colors were perfect and photographed beautifully. I cannot imagine the day without August Lily Florist's hard work and passion! Hope to work together soon!
I always come every year to get my wife flowers for our anniversary and they never fail to amaze me on the flower arrangements. Would highly recommend!!
We had a lovely birthday delivery of a fiddle leaf fig sent from a relative. We were also offered to exchange the decorations if we wanted! Thank you so much!
This is the best little flower shop. Cute fun gifts too!

I placed an order on December 23rd to be delivered on the 24th and they were (expectedly) out of some of the flowers in the arrangement.  They called and offered a “designers choice” and they really came through!  Gorgeous arrangement and incredible customer service.  They even texted me a picture before the arrangement went out to make sure it was acceptable!  Highly recommend!
Always a great experience!
Great service and selection.
Great customet service superior product
This is a very cute floral shop! The ladies there are really nice. They have a nice assortment of specialty gifts and home decor...I will go back..

I am super disappointed with this florist. I had ordered flowers for an event in which I am not present for. I was relying on reviews and the website. I was comfortable until I couldn’t get a hold of them the following morning to ensure delivery. I then had to find another reputable florist in the area to take care of me. I called the Petal Shoppe and they were amazing.
